                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="16754" author="olsoner" created="Fri, 10 Mar 2006 06:58:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I misspoke - can&apos;t override OncePerRequest#getFilterName().   I&apos;m not extending OncePerRequestFilter.  I just found the problem because I created my own OncePerSessionFilter, which is the same as OncePerRequestFilter except that it stores an &quot;already filtered&quot; attribute in session rather than request.  So my OncePerSessionFilter#getFilterName() uses the bean name like I described.  Either way, the same issue still exists with OncePerRequestFilter.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16876" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Mon, 20 Mar 2006 18:33:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for pointing this out!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve refined GenericFilterBean to explicitly support initialization as bean in a Spring bean factory as well. This means that getFilterName() and getServletContext() now fall back to values provided by the setBeanName and setServletContext callbacks, respectively - for the case where the filter is not initialized with a FilterConfig instance. This allows all subclasses, including OncePerRequestFilter, to run without a FilterConfig as well.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
